transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling DIAGRA, how can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Hey, I keep getting bills for it, but I never get nothing sent to me.

Speaker 1: It was supposed to cancel my order, and then the girl decided she was going to send me like nine free pills or something.

Speaker 2: But I've gotten billed four times for this thing.

Speaker 1: What is your name and date of birth?

Speaker 2: It's Henry Billis, October 10, 1963.

Speaker 1: Thank you, Henry.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, so it looks like you are a VIP with us, so you do have a prescription with us,

Speaker 1: which is why you continue to receive orders.

Speaker 2: So you are – you do have a prescription for DIAGRA, and you receive a quantity of ten.

Speaker 1: I haven't received – I've only received one, and I've been billed four times already for this thing.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but you've been refunded for the other time.

Speaker 1: Well, I've only been refunded one time.

Speaker 2: I've only been refunded once.

Speaker 1: I only see one that was odd.

Speaker 2: I'm looking at my credit card statement right here.

Speaker 1: I was refunded odd.

Speaker 2: Let's see, I'll tell you the date.

Speaker 1: Well, I mean, last time you called in to pause your prescription for half a year, so it's been paused.

Speaker 2: So I don't want to pause it.

Speaker 1: I want to just stop it.

Speaker 2: I don't want to get billed anymore for this.

Speaker 1: It doesn't work anymore.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, just be aware that you're not going to be able to reorder with us in the future, okay?

Speaker 1: Well, that's fine.

Speaker 2: Okay, you're all set.

Speaker 1: Have a nice day, Henry.

Speaker 2: Bye.
